<p class="pagesubtitle">The agile IAM for DevOps</p>

<p>
  <strong>Authorized Entities Directory (&AElig;-DIR)</strong>
  is a Privileged Identity and Access Management (IAM/PIM/PAM)
  based on <a href="https://www.openldap.org">OpenLDAP</a>
</p>

{% if aedir_news %}
<p id="news" class="pagesubtitle">
  News:
</p>
<ul>
{% for news_item in aedir_news %}
    <li>{{ news_item }}</li>
{% endfor %}
</ul>
{% endif %}

<p id="objectives" class="pagesubtitle">
  Main Objectives
</p>
<ul>
  <li>Strictly follow <strong>need to know</strong> and <strong>least privilege</strong> principles</li>
  <li>Agile data maintenance by consequent delegation of manageable small areas</li>
  <li>Provide meaningful audit trails for compliance checks</li>
  <li>Secure defaults</li>
</ul>

<p id="key-features" class="pagesubtitle">
  Key Features
</p>
<ul>
  <li>Fine-grained authorization</a></li>
  <li>Fine-grained delegation, ready-to-use role-model</li>
  <li>Role separation, multiple accounts per person</li>
  <li>Secure password handling, SSH key distribution</li>
  <li>Compatible to all LDAP enabled applications</li>
  <li>Two-factor authentication integrated with LDAP</li>
  <li>High availability out-of-the-box with LDAP server replicas</li>
  <li>TLS everywhere</li>
  <li>Service hardening out-of-the-box</li>
</ul>

<p>
  Find longer introductions:
  <a href="https://stroeder.com/publications.html">
  &AElig;-DIR conference presentations</a>.
</p>

{% endblock content %}
